### CREATE THE POST

> cd ~/myblog
> hugo new posts/my-new-post.md
> Change the front matter
> Write the post
> Preview locally
    >hugo server > Click localhost link

### HANDLING IMAGES

For previews:
In the metadata (front matter) include:

image = "cover.jpg"  # or full path like "images/tyov/cover.jpg"

### WHERE DO THEY LIVE
Option A - Page Bundle (recommended): content/posts/tyov-entry-1/cover.jpg
Option B - Static folder: static/images/tyov/cover.jpg (then use image = "images/tyov/cover.jpg")

For 

### TELL GIT TO WHICH FILES YOU WANT TO INCLUDE IN THE NEXT COMMIT

> git add content/posts/my-new-post.md

OR

> git add . # Will include any and all changes rather than a specific file.


### COMMIT THE CHANGE
> git commit -m "Add new post"
# -m means "message"

### PUSH THE CHANGE
git push


### 
Think of GitHub + Hugo as a “build-and-publish machine”:

Write → local files only

git add → mark files to include

git commit → snapshot for the machine

git push → send snapshot to GitHub

GitHub Actions → rebuild site → live HTML

Visitors see the new post
###



